The crucial step in QSSM is the unique determination of the 96\times96 finite Dirac operator (D_F). This is achieved by imposing the discrete Grand Symmetry of \mathbb{Z}_2\times\mathbb{Z}_2\times\mathbb{Z}_3 at the unification scale \Lambda_{\text{unif}} \approx 10^{14} \text{ GeV}.
