1.4 Torsion-Driven Mass Hierarchy
The generational mass hierarchy is derived from the analytic torsion of a discrete \mathbb{Z}_3 action on the lens space L(3,1). The suppression factor is determined by the logarithm of the torsion ratio \log(|\mathcal{T}_k / \mathcal{T}_0|):
where R_k = \phi^{2k} determines the mass ratio \frac{m_k}{m_0} = \exp\!\bigg(-\frac{\pi^2}{6}\cdot k(3-k)/R_k\bigg).
| k | Generation | Final Torsion Exponent | Mass Ratio m_k/m_0 |
|---|---|---|---|
| 0 | Third (t,\tau) | 0 | 1 |
